    <main class="container">
        <section>
            <h2 id="what-are-stocks">What are Stocks?</h2>
            <p>Stocks are an investment method to build wealth. When you invest in the stock of a company, it means you own a share in the company that issued the stock.</p>
            <p>Stocks are categorized based on:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Market capitalization</li>
                <li>Ownership</li>
                <li>Fundamentals</li>
                <li>Price volatility</li>
                <li>Profit sharing</li>
                <li>Economic trends</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 id="share-market">What is Share Market?</h2>
            <p>The share market is where shares are issued or traded. Companies raise money by selling ownership stakes to investors. These stakes are known as shares of stock.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 id="market-timings">Stock Market Timings</h2>
            <p>The stock market in India operates on weekdays (Monday to Friday) during the following sessions:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Pre-Opening Session:</strong> 9:00 AM to 9:15 AM</li>
                <li><strong>Regular Trading Session:</strong> 9:15 AM to 3:30 PM</li>
                <li><strong>Post-Closing Session:</strong> 3:30 PM to 4:00 PM</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Note: Stock markets remain closed on weekends and public holidays.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 id="important-terms">Understanding the Stock Market Basics - Important Terms</h2>
            <div class="glossary-grid">
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>Sensex:</strong> A collection of the top 30 stocks listed on the BSE by way of market capitalization.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>SEBI:</strong> The Securities and Exchange Board of India oversees the securities market.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>Demat:</strong> An online portfolio that holds shares and securities in electronic format.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>Trading:</strong> The process of buying or selling shares in a company.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>Stock Index:</strong> A statistical source measuring financial market fluctuations.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>Portfolio:</strong> A collection of assets owned by investors.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>IPO:</strong> Initial Public Offer, a process where companies offer securities to the public for the first time.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>BSE:</strong> Bombay Stock Exchange, the first securities exchange market in India.</div>
                <div class="glossary-item"><strong>NSE:</strong> National Stock Exchange, known for electronic trading in India.</div>
            </div>
        </section>
